From Welch Bryan Subject Re warranty extension by credit company applies to the phurchase of computer In article Ken Staggers writes HUAYONG YANG wrote Most if not all credit card companies offer to double the warranty up to one year namely if you make a purchase by a credit card you get additional warranty up to one Does it apply to the purchase of computers I wonder if anyone out there has used Is there any catch Thanks in I am just about to post the results of my big computer One of the key points was the ability to use my American Express I read the fine print between double warranty policies of Amex and Citibank Sure both will allow you double warranty on computers but Citibank has a maximum claim of Could you imagine trying to get your monitor or mother board fixed for Amex has NO limit on Remember if you use Amex you must either send a copy of the warranty info to them in days from purchase or you must call them to pre register and then send them the paperwork within days of purchase my pre register pak arrived today Citibank VISA requires no pre Ken I just talked to a rep for my AT T mastercard regarding this There is no maximum claim and you only have to notify them of the warranty when the item needs If it can't be repaired you get the amount you paid for Curiously though the AT T Gold mastercard has a limit of on Definitely not upgrading to that Bryan Bryan Welch Amateur Radio Internet best Everything will perish save love and Scots Gaelic proverb